# Security: Collaboration and Data Handling

## Encryption

- Room key MUST stay in the URL fragment (`#`) only — NEVER send it to the server
- AES encryption is mandatory for all data transmitted via Socket.io portal
- Do NOT log or expose the room key in console output, error messages, or analytics

## Input Validation

- NEVER pass unsanitized user input directly to `eval()`, `innerHTML`, `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`, or `new Function()`
- URL parameters and URL fragment values must be validated before use
- Firebase paths must be constructed from validated IDs only — no user-controlled string concatenation

## Dependency Safety

- Do NOT add packages that process untrusted data (parsers, deserializers) without security review
- Before importing a new parser (JSON, SVG, image), verify it has no known CVEs via `npm audit`

## Secrets

- Firebase config values come from environment variables only (`VITE_APP_FIREBASE_CONFIG`)
- `.env.local` is gitignored — NEVER commit secrets to the repo

## How to verify

1. Run `grep -r "dangerouslySetInnerHTML\|eval(" excalidraw-app/` — any result requires immediate review
2. Run `grep -r "roomKey\|roomID" excalidraw-app/collab/Portal.tsx` — confirm the key is never included in server payload (check `broadcastScene`, `broadcastMouseLocation` calls)
3. Run `git log --all --full-history -- "**/.env*"` — confirm no `.env.local` or `.env.production` was ever committed
4. Run `npm audit` — zero high/critical vulnerabilities allowed in `excalidraw-app` dependencies
